HEADWORD: locoism
<hw>locoism</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <def>a disease of livestock caused by
locoweed poisoning; characterized by weakness and lack of coordination
and trembling and partial paralysis.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> loco disease.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

